<p><strong>3. Why is it important to study human histology?</strong></p>
<p>Human histology is the study of the microscopic structure of human tissues. It is essential for understanding the normal function of the human body and for diagnosing and treating disease. Histology is used in a variety of clinical settings, including pathology, surgery, and dermatology.</p>
<p><strong>4. What are some of the clinical applications of human histology?</strong></p>
<p>Human histology is used to:</p>
<ul>
<li>Diagnose and classify diseases</li>
<li>Determine the prognosis of a disease</li>
<li>Guide treatment decisions</li>
<li>Monitor the response to treatment</li>
</ul>
